comment: it must be the name of one of the built-in datatypes defined in section 5.11.1 Built-in Datatypes

name: datatype @id an absolute URL
comment: If included, @id is a link property that identifies the datatype described by this datatype description.

name: date format (valid time combinations with formats and milliseconds)
comment: The supported date and time formats listed here are expressed in terms of the date field symbols defined in [UAX35] and MUST be interpreted by implementations as defined in that specification.

name: date format (valid dateTime combinations with formats and milliseconds)

name: Unicode in non-Normalized form

name: tree-ops example with csvm.json (w3.org/.well-known/csvm)
comment: Processors MUST use the first metadata found for processing a tabular data file by using overriding metadata, if provided. Otherwise processors MUST attempt to locate the first metadata document from the Link header or the metadata located through site-wide configuration.

name: tree-ops example with {+url}.json (w3.org/.well-known/csvm)
comment: Processors MUST use the first metadata found for processing a tabular data file by using overriding metadata, if provided. Otherwise processors MUST attempt to locate the first metadata document from the Link header or the metadata located through site-wide configuration.

name: @type on a common property can be a built-in type
comment: The value of any member of `@type` MUST be either a _term_ defined in [csvw-context], a _prefixed name_ where the prefix is a term defined in [csvw-context], or an absolute URL.

name: @type on a common property can be a CURIE if the prefix is one of the built-in ones
comment: The value of any member of `@type` MUST be either a _term_ defined in [csvw-context], a _prefixed name_ where the prefix is a term defined in [csvw-context], or an absolute URL.

name: `null` contains an array of (valid) string & (invalid) numeric values
comment: Processors MUST issue a warning if a property is set to an invalid value type

name: `base` missing on datatype (defaults to string)
comment: An atomic property that contains a single string: the name of one of the built-in datatypes, as listed above (and which are defined as terms in the default context). Its default is string.

name: `format` for a boolean datatype is a string but in the wrong form (eg YN)
comment: If the datatype base for a cell is `boolean`, the datatype format annotation provides the true value followed by the false value, separated by `|`. If the format does not follow this syntax, implementations MUST issue a warning and proceed as if no format had been provided.

name: transformation includes an invalid property (eg foo)
comment: All terms used within a metadata document MUST be defined in [csvw-context] defined for this specification

name: `@base` set in `@context` overriding eg CSV location
comment: If present, its value MUST be a string that is interpreted as a URL which is resolved against the location of the metadata document to provide the **base URL** for other URLs in the metadata document.

name: property acceptable on column appears on table group
comment: Table Group may only use defined properties.

name: property acceptable on column appears on table
comment: Table may only use defined properties.

name: property acceptable on table appears on column
comment: Column may only use defined properties.

name: CSV has more headers than there are columns in the metadata
comment: Two schemas are compatible if they have the same number of non-virtual column descriptions, and the non-virtual column descriptions at the same index within each are compatible with each other.

name: duration not matching xsd pattern
comment: Value MUST be a valid xsd:duration.

name: dayTimeDuration not matching xsd pattern
comment: Value MUST be a valid xsd:dayTimeDuration.

name: yearMonthDuration not matching xsd pattern
comment: Value MUST be a valid xsd:yearMonthDuration.
